  title `Short title and local extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879&sectionId=43442&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Live-stock Importation Act, 1898.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***;] ^3***,`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 40 of 1953, s. 2, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f.1-11-`
  line `1956).`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (3) rep. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43443)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879&sectionId=43443&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "infectious or contagious disorders" includes tick-pest, anthrax, glanders,`
  line `farcy, scabies and any other disease or disorder which may be specified by the Central`
  line `Government by notification in the Official Gazette; and`
  line
  line `(b) "live-stock" includes horses, kine, camels, sheep and any other animal which may be`
  line `specified by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette ;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) "import" means the bringing or taking, by sea, land or air into ^2[India].]`
  line
  line `^3[(d) "live-stock products" include meat and meat products of all kinds includ­ing fresh, chilled`
  line `and frozen meat, tissue, organs of poultry, pig, sheep, goat; egg and egg powder, milk and milk`
  line `products; bovine, ovine and caprine, embryos, ova, semen; pet food products of animal origin and`
  line `any other animal product which may be specified by the Central Government by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1953, s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule for the territories to which this Act extends (w.e.f.1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 5-7-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43444)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to regulate importation of live-stock.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879&sectionId=43444&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, regulate, restrict or prohibit, in such manner and to such extent as`
  line `it may think fit, ^2[the import], into ^1[India] or any specified place therein, of any livestock which may`
  line `be liable to be affected by infectious or contagious disorders, and of any fodder, dung, stable-litter,`
  line `clothing harness or fittings appertaining to live-stock or that may have been in contact therewith.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) A notification under sub-section (1) shall operate as if it had been issued under section 19 of`
  line `the Sea Customs Act, 1878 (8 of 1878), and the officers of customs at every port shall have the same`
  line `power in respect of any live-stock or thing, with regard to 'the importation of which such a`
  line `notification has been issued, and the vessel containing the same, as they have for the time being in`
  line `respect of any article the importation of which is regulated restricted or prohibited by the law relating`
  line `to sea customs and the vessel containing the same; and the enactments for the time being in force`
  line `relating to sea customs or any such article or vessel shall apply accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1953, s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Ad 40 of 1953, s. 4, for "the bringing or taking, by sea or land".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 2001, s. 4, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 5-7-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (49375)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to regulate Importation of live-stock products.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2001, s. 5 (w.e.f. 5-7-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879&sectionId=49375&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Power to regulate Importation of live-stock products. --The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, regulate, restrict or prohibit in such manner and to such extent`
  line `as it may think fit, the import into the territories to which this Act extends, of any live-stock product,`
  line `which may be liable to affect human or animal health.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43445)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. The words "subject to the control of the Governor-General in Council" omitted by the A.O.1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879&sectionId=43445&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may ^1*** make rules`
  line `for the detention, inspection, disinfection of destruction of imported live-stock, and of fodder, dung,`
  line `stable-litter, clothing harness or fittings appertaining to imported live-stock or that may have been in`
  line `contact therewith and for regulating the powers and duties of the officers whom it may appoint in this`
  line behalf..
  line
  line `(2) In making any rule under this section the State Government may direct that a breach thereof`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43446)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Protection to persons acting under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879&sectionId=43446&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_189809_1523338057879
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
